=== 汤加 ===
12月30日，包括[[斐济|斐济]]和[[萨摩亚|萨摩亚]]部分岛屿在内的许多岛上收到警报，这时距风暴来袭还有一天时间。天气预报显示，风暴会以三级气旋强度直接从汤加地势低洼的[[首都|首都]][[努库阿洛法|努库阿洛法]]上空经过<ref>{{cite web | author = Agence France-Presse | work = United Nations | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2001-12-30 | accessdate = 2014-11-15 | title = Severe cyclone bearing down on South Pacific islands | archivedate = 2013-09-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130906114007/http://reliefweb.int/report/fiji/severe-cyclone-bearing-down-south-pacific-islands | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/fiji/severe-cyclone-bearing-down-south-pacific-islands}}</ref>。由于当地媒体及时发布警报<ref>{{cite web | author = Agence France-Presse | publisher = ReliefWeb | work = United Nations | date = 2001-12-31 | accessdate = 2014-11-15 | title = South Pacific cyclone intensifies — Tonga at risk | archivedate = 2013-08-11 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130811143717/http://reliefweb.int/report/fiji/south-pacific-cyclone-intensifies-tonga-risk | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/fiji/south-pacific-cyclone-intensifies-tonga-risk | deadurl = no}}</ref>，所有的[[跨年|跨年]]庆祝活动均予取消，当地居民和游客纷纷返回屋内并将房屋加固。该区域所有的机场均予关闭，轮渡服务也暂时中止<ref>{{cite news | author = Paul Yandall | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-01 | accessdate = 2014-11-15 | title = Tonga battens down as Cyclone Waka roars in | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584650 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129010829/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584650 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。面积仅有约35[[平方公里|平方公里]]的[[纽阿福欧岛|纽阿福欧岛]]有许多居民在风暴来袭前撤离到其他岛上<ref>{{cite news | work = The Dominion | date = 2002-01-02 | title = Cyclone Waka heads out into Pacific after lashing Tonga | location = Wellington, New Zealand}}</ref>。

[[File:Cyclone_Waka_passing_over_Tonga.jpg|thumb]]卫星图像。]]

风暴经过汤加期间，只有少数岛屿记录下的风速达到飓风强度，[[内亚富|内亚富]]测得的风速最强，达到每小时185公里。南部岛屿中有局部地区出现时速高达250公里的阵风。[[哈派群岛|哈派群岛]]的持续风速有100公里，阵风时速140公里。<ref>{{cite news | work = The Press | date = 2002-01-02 | title = Cyclone Waka Batters Tonga | location = Wellington, New Zealand}}</ref>瓦卡途经期间多地降下暴雨，哈派群岛降雨量超过200毫米<ref name="RW2">{{cite web | work = United Nations | author = East-West Center | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-01-03 | accessdate = 2011-04-13 | title = Damage from Cyclone Waka to Vava'u runs in millions of Pa'anga | archivedate = 2013-09-10 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130910083743/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-damage-cyclone-waka-vavau-runs-millions-paanga | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-damage-cyclone-waka-vavau-runs-millions-paanga}}</ref>。

12月31日，努库阿洛法的初步报告表明当地农业受灾严重，但[[基础设施|基础设施]]遭受的破坏很小<ref>{{cite web | author = United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2010-12-31 | accessdate = 2014-11-15 | title = Tonga — Tropical Cyclone Waka OCHA Situation Report No. 1 | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-tropical-cyclone-waka-ocha-situation-report-no-1 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923154307/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-tropical-cyclone-waka-ocha-situation-report-no-1}}</ref>。风暴过去后，纽阿斯和[[瓦瓦乌群岛|瓦瓦乌群岛]]的通讯中断<ref>{{cite web | work = United Nations | author = Agence France-Presse | publisher = R eliefWeb | date = 2002-01-01 | accessdate = 2014-11-15 | title = Tongas northern group hit by cyclone — heavy damage feared | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tongas-northern-group-hit-cyclone-heavy-damage-feared | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131031215704/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tongas-northern-group-hit-cyclone-heavy-damage-feared | archivedate = 2013-10-31}}</ref>。根据地方报告，内亚富狂风肆虐，在全市范围卷起沙尘的同时还刮倒了几乎所有的树<ref name="RW1">{{cite web | author = Deutsche Presse Agentur | work = United Nations | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130913204513/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/new-zealand-air-force-sending-plane-check-tonga-cyclone-damage | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-01-01 | accessdate = 2011-04-13 | title = New Zealand Air Force sending plane to check Tonga cyclone damage | archivedate = 2013-09-13 | deadurl = no | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/new-zealand-air-force-sending-plane-check-tonga-cyclone-damage}}</ref>。[[国际红十字与红新月运动|红十字会]]的统计调查表明，该市有约200套民房不是被毁就是严重受损，剩下的房屋则大多失去了屋顶<ref name="RW3">{{cite web | author = Reuters | work = United Nations | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-01-03 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Red Cross seeks food aid after Tonga cyclone | archivedate = 2012-09-23 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923154535/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/red-cross-seeks-food-aid-after-tonga-cyclone | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/red-cross-seeks-food-aid-after-tonga-cyclone | deadurl = no}}</ref>。瓦瓦乌群岛失去了约90%的庄稼，其中包括[[芋|芋头]]、[[山药|山药]]和[[香蕉|香蕉]]这样的重要粮食作物。哈派群岛有一人在风暴期间因[[心停止|心脏骤停]]死亡。倒塌的树木阻塞了许多道路，大部分居民区的水电供应均遭切断。[[纽阿托普塔普岛|纽阿托普塔普岛]]也受到严重破坏，许多沿海民居受到瓦卡产生的[[风暴潮|风暴潮]]冲击{{#tag:ref|[[风暴潮|风暴潮]]指平均潮汐高度和风暴产生潮汐高度之间的差距<ref name="glos">{{cite report | publisher = National Hurricane Center | date = 2013-03-25 | accessdate = 2014-06-15 | title = Glossary of NHC Terms | archivedate = 2014-06-01 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140601020814/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/aboutgloss.shtml | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/aboutgloss.shtml}}</ref>。|group="注"}}，大量建筑物失去屋顶<ref name="RW2" />。一艘[[游艇|游艇]]被潮水冲到岸上并撞入一家餐馆，最后游艇和餐馆都完全被毁<ref>{{cite news | author = Paul Yandall | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-02 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Battered Tonga struggles to mop up | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584778 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129023149/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584778 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

灾害评估报告表明，汤加有13个岛受到破坏<ref name="Bats">{{cite journal | author = Kim R. McConkey, Donald R. Drake, Janet Franklin and Filipe Tonga | year = 2004 | title = Effects of Cyclone Waka on flying foxes (''Pteropus tonganus'') in the Vava'u Islands of Tonga | journal = Journal of Tropical Ecology | volume = 20 | issue = 5 | pages = 555–561 | publisher = Cambridge University Press | doi = 10.1017/S0266467404001804 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121022160439/http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=240809 | url = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=240809 | archivedate = 2012-10-22}}</ref>，470套民房和6所学校被毁，另有数百套房屋受损<ref name="RNZ1">{{cite news | work = Radio New Zealand International | date = 2002-01-08 | title = New Zealand to give Tonga 700,000 dollars for cyclone relief}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Emily McKenzie, Biman Prasad and Atu Kaloumaira |publisher=Australian Agency for International Development |date=2005-05 |accessdate=2014-11-16 |title=Economic Impact of Natural Disaster on Development in the Pacific |page=65 |archivedate=2013-09-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060224/http://www.pacificdisaster.net/pdnadmin/data/original/economic%20impact%20of%20natural%20disasters%20on%20development%20in%20the%20pacific.pdf |url=http://www.pacificdisaster.net/pdnadmin/data/original/economic%20impact%20of%20natural%20disasters%20on%20development%20in%20the%20pacific.pdf }}</ref>。全国受到的损失价值1.042亿[[汤加潘加|汤加潘加]]（相当于5130万[[美元|美元]]）<ref>{{cite web | author = Center for Research on the Epidemiology of Disasters | year = 2010 | accessdate = 2013-12-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131203010145/http://www.emdat.be/disaster-list | title = International Disaster Database: Disaster List | url = http://www.emdat.be/disaster-list | archivedate = 2013-12-03 | deadurl = yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs |publisher=Center for International Disaster Information |date=2002-01-23 |accessdate=2011-09-27 |title=OCHA Situation Report No. 2 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927103238/http://www.cidi.org/report/5532 |url=http://www.cidi.org/report/5532 |archivedate=2011-09-27 }}</ref>。除基础设施和公共财产损失外，汤加的环境也遭受到灾难性破坏。当地有大量原生[[海岛狐蝠|海岛狐蝠]]物种在风暴期间死亡，在共计6个岛上的数量减少了79.8%（±9.9%）。这主要是因为其天然食物来源受到大范围破坏，食物在风暴过后减少了85%（±11.8%）。瓦瓦乌群岛的所有树木都[[落叶剂|掉光了树叶]]，<ref name="Bats" />有6.6%的树木死亡<ref name="Trees" />，导致蝙蝠没有食物。所有岛屿中蝙蝠数量下量比例最大的高达95.7%，有些岛上所有能为蝙蝠提供食物的植物全部消失。风暴过去6个月后，瓦瓦乌群岛的蝙蝠数量仍然只达到风暴前约20%的水平。<ref name="Bats" />

=== 其他地区 ===
气旋形成阶段给[[托克劳群岛|托克劳群岛]]带去狂风大浪，引发局部洪灾和农作物损失。[[美属萨摩亚|美属萨摩亚]]也出现暴雨，降雨量约56.9毫米，阵风时速90公里<ref name="WMOFinal" />。狂风刮倒了少量树木，造成轻度农作物损失，数额约为12万美元<ref>{{cite web | work = National Climatic Data Center | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | year = 2013 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = American Samoa Event Report: High Wind | archivedate = 2014-11-16 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141116094400/http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5274493 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5274493}}</ref>。由于天气系统发展缓慢，等到风暴逐渐离开该区域时，群岛已经受到持续约一星期的大浪影响<ref>{{cite web | work = National Climatic Data Center | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | year = 2013 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = American Samoa Event Report: High Surf | url = http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5274495 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141116095049/http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5274495 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | work = National Climatic Data Center | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | year = 2013 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = American Samoa Event Report: High Surf | url = http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5278165 | archivedate = 2014-11-16 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141116095142/http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=5278165}}</ref>。瓦卡还对[[瓦利斯和富图纳|瓦利斯和富图纳]]构成影响，当地从12月28日至31日收到了[[热带气旋警告|热带气旋警告]]；之后又冲击了[[纽埃|纽埃]]，当地警报从12月30日起生效直至次年1月1日止<ref name="NadiATCR">{{cite report | publisher = Fiji Meteorological Service | author = RSMC Nadi — Tropical Cyclone Centre | title = Tropical Cyclone Summary 2001-2002 Season}}</ref>。[[瓦利斯岛|瓦利斯岛]]上有一套民房被毁，50%的香蕉作物付诸东流<ref name="GPsum" />。[[马塔乌图机场|希希福]]在气旋途经期间降雨量最高，达112毫米<ref>{{cite web | publisher = Meteo France | year = 2010 | accessdate = 2012-03-20 | title = Cyclones passés | url = http://www.meteo.nc/index.php?option=com_cyclones&view=cyclones&Itemid=99 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120320103439/http://www.meteo.nc/index.php?option=com_cyclones&view=cyclones&Itemid=99 | archivedate = 2012-03-20}}</ref>。瓦利斯岛记录下时速126公里阵风，涌浪则高达7米。纽埃遭受的破坏更大，风暴潮高达8米，海浪冲入内陆达100米远。大量树木倒塌，输电线缆中断，许多道路因此封堵，岛上南部地区电力中断约6小时<ref name="GPsum" />。纽埃遭受的损失总额约为1万美元<ref name="WMOFinal">{{cite report | publisher = World Meteorological Organization | date = 2002-05-20 | title = RA V Tropical Cyclone Committee for the South Pacific and South-East Indian Ocean Ninth Session: Final Report}}</ref>。

经过汤加群岛后，风暴残留给[[新西兰|新西兰]][[北岛_(新西兰)|北岛]]带去高达2.5米的涌浪。因适逢新年假期，这一地区有数以千计的居民和游客。[[气象学家|气象专家]]警告海上会越来越危险，呼吁市民不要冒险下水。[[旺格玛塔|旺格玛塔]]（{{lang|en|Whangamata}}）所有的救生员和以前曾从事过救生员工作的人都被调来提供协助，确保约8000人不会下水<ref>{{cite news | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-04 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Cyclone whips up surf scare on beaches | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/marine/news/article.cfm?c_id=61&objectid=585039 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129035732/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/marine/news/article.cfm?c_id=61&objectid=585039 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。大部分决定入水游泳的人们都待在指定泳区内，但救生员仍然不得不对多位遇险人员实施救援<ref>{{cite news | author = Josie Clark | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-05 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Big waves create busy day for lifeguards | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/marine/news/article.cfm?c_id=61&objectid=585238 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129035727/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/marine/news/article.cfm?c_id=61&objectid=585238 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。芒格努伊山的主海滩有38人被[[离岸流|离岸流]]卷入海中，幸运的是他们都很快得到救生员的帮助<ref>{{cite news | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-05 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = 38 swimmers rescued off Mt. Maunganui Beach | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=585261 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129035724/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=585261 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

== 善后 ==
[[File:Waka_2001_track_near_Tonga.png|thumb]]
气旋瓦卡离开汤加后还不到一天，新西兰政府就派出飞机前去评估灾害规模，并与汤加群岛重新建立联系<ref name="RW1" />。[[法国|法国]]、[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]和新西兰曾于1992年签署《弗朗兹协定》，规定在[[南太平洋|南太平洋]]地区出现自然灾害后，几个国家都会利用本国资源援助救灾，新西兰政府正是根据这一协定的要求派出飞机<ref>{{cite news | publisher = Embassy of France in Papua New Guinea | year = 2010 | title = The FRANZ Agreement | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090914101637/http://www.ambafrance-pg.org/article.php3?id_article=378 | archivedate = 2009-09-14 | url = http://www.ambafrance-pg.org/article.php3?id_article=378}}</ref>。1月2日，汤加救灾办公室主任宣布，该国很可能需要国际援助来应对风暴的善后工作<ref>{{cite web | author = Australian Broadcasting Corporation | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-01-02 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tongan authorities assess damage from cyclone Waka | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tongan-authorities-assess-damage-cyclone-waka | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130910223233/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tongan-authorities-assess-damage-cyclone-waka | archivedate = 2013-09-10}}</ref>。汤加的农业在这场风暴中遭受重创，预计之后数月也都面临饥荒的威胁<ref name="RW2" /><ref name="FoodShortageApril" />。到1月7日时，[[国际红十字与红新月运动|红十字会]]已开始向该国运送物资。澳大利亚派出[[AC-130空中砲艇|AC-130空中砲艇]]送来数以百计的帐篷和防水油布，协助救灾工作<ref>{{cite news | author = Francesca Mold | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-07 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tonga picks up the pieces left by Cyclone Waka | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=585395 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129010832/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=585395 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1月12日，一架新西兰[[C-130运输机|C-130运输机]]满载价值70万美元的物资飞抵这一地区提供援助<ref>{{cite news | publisher = BBC News | date = 2002-01-12 | title = New Zealand air force drops off relief supplies to cyclone-hit Tonga}}</ref>。此外，新西兰还提供了70万美元救灾资金用于修复风暴造成的破坏。这其中有50万美元用来修复受损或被毁的学校，剩下的20万美元则用于恢复应急照明、烹饪和食品供应<ref name="RNZ1" /><ref>{{cite news | work = The Press | date = 2002-01-09 | title = NZ offers $700,000 to Tonga | location = Wellington, New Zealand}}</ref>。

[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]]于2002年1月中旬提供了2.5万美元资金<ref>{{cite web | archivedate = 2013-09-11 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130911150359/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-us-donates-25k-cyclone-relief | deadurl = no | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-us-donates-25k-cyclone-relief | author = Pacific Islands Broadcasting Association | publisher = ReliefWeb | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tonga: US donates $25k for cyclone relief | date = 2002-01-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=United States Agency for International Development |year=2002 |accessdate=2014-11-16 |title=Annual Report for the 2002 Fiscal Year |archivedate=2012-03-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304024248/http://cidbimena.desastres.hn/docum/crid/Julio2006/CD2/pdf/eng/doc14930/doc14930-3c.pdf |url=http://cidbimena.desastres.hn/docum/crid/Julio2006/CD2/pdf/eng/doc14930/doc14930-3c.pdf |format=PDF }}</ref>。[[大溪地|大溪地]]的[[法属玻里尼西亚|法属玻里尼西亚]]居民也一起提供了77万美元的救灾物资和援助金<ref>{{cite web | author = Pacific Islands Broadcasting Association | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-01-21 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tahiti approves US$770,000 Tonga aid package | archivedate = 2014-11-29 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129221440/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tahiti-approves-us770000-tonga-aid-package | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tahiti-approves-us770000-tonga-aid-package }}</ref>。[[旅游业|旅游业]]是汤加的经济支柱，但由于这场风暴的影响，游客在风暴过后至少两个星期内都被禁止前往这一区域，令当地经济雪上加霜<ref>{{cite news | author = Paul Yandall | work = The New Zealand Herald | date = 2002-01-03 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = NZ ready with food for Tonga | url = http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584902 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129010822/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=584902 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。汤加政府一共加国际社会请求了3920万美元援助，其中大部分都是用于修复基础设施。[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]之后还向该国提供了医疗物资和人员<ref>{{cite web | author = United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-02-06 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tropical Cyclone Waka OCHA Situation Report No. 3 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-tropical-cyclone-waka-ocha-situation-report-no-3 | archivedate = 2013-09-13 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130913121335/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/tonga-tropical-cyclone-waka-ocha-situation-report-no-3}}</ref>。3月上旬，[[联合卫理公会救济委员会|联合卫理公会救济委员会]]用捐款设立救灾基金，向30户受灾家庭提供21万美元援助<ref>{{cite web|publisher=United Methodist Committee on Relief |date=2002-03-01 |accessdate=2014-11-16 |title=The UMCOR Hotline |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120309164108/http://gbgm-umc.org/umcor-hotline/20020301.cfm |deadurl=yes |url=http://gbgm-umc.org/umcor-hotline/20020301.cfm |archivedate=2012-03-09 }}</ref>。3月下旬，[[基督教会世界服务社|基督教会世界服务社]]向约180人提供援助，帮助他们重建家园<ref>{{cite web | author = Unattributed | work = Church World Service | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2002-03-18 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = CWS helps vulnerable families rebuild cyclone-destroyed houses in Tonga | archivedate = 2013-09-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130911024305/http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/cws-helps-vulnerable-families-rebuild-cyclone-destroyed-houses-tonga | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/tonga/cws-helps-vulnerable-families-rebuild-cyclone-destroyed-houses-tonga}}</ref>。4月，纽阿斯的粮食短缺已经非常严重，紧急救援物资因此送到了该岛<ref name="FoodShortageApril">{{cite web |author=Staff Writer |work=Marianas Variety |date=2002-04-10 |accessdate=2011-02-19 |title=Tonga ships food to Niuas |url=http://www.mvariety.com/community-bulletin/tonga-ships-food-to-niuas.php |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wcLhjGL3?url=http://www.mvariety.com/community-bulletin/tonga-ships-food-to-niuas.php |archivedate=2011-02-19 }}</ref>。5月，[[世界银行|世界银行]]批准向该国提供585万美元应急资金，用于协助重建基础设施<ref>{{cite report | title = Tonga, 2002 Article IV consultation: staff report, public information notice on the Executive Board discussion, and statement by the Executive Director for Tonga | date = 2003-02-27 | publisher = International Monetary Fund | url = http://www.imf.org/external/pubs/cat/longres.aspx?sk=16345.0 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | page = 5 | issn = 1934-7685 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129013046/http://www.imf.org/external/pubs/cat/longres.aspx?sk=16345.0 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

瓦瓦乌群岛的农产品出口出现大幅削减，与前一年相比减少了86.5%<ref>{{cite report | publisher = Tonga. Ministry of Agriculture | title = Report of the Ministry of Agriculture for the year 2002 | year = 2002 | page = 172}}</ref>。虽然农业遭受受创，但该国总体经济到2002年底还是增长了2.9%，同时农业部门也扩充了约2%<ref>{{cite book | title = Small States: Economic Review & Basic Statistics | year = 2004 | publisher = Commonwealth Secretariat | isbn = 978-0-85092-794-8 | url = http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Small_States.html?id=8yJGO1WvaO4C | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | page = 20 | archive-date = 2014-11-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141129040642/http://books.google.com.hk/books/about/Small_States.html?id=8yJGO1WvaO4C | dead-url = no }}</ref>。由于这场风暴造成了重大损失，[[世界气象组织|世界气象组织]]将其名称“瓦卡”退役，并用“维基”取代<ref>{{cite web | author = unattributed | publisher = World Meteorological Organization | year = 2008 | accessdate = 2014-11-16 | title = Tropical Cyclone Operation Plan for the South Pacific and South-East Indian Ocean | archivedate = 2013-12-07 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131207114934/http://www.wmo.int/pages/prog/www/tcp/documents/TCP24-English2008.pdf | url = http://www.wmo.int/pages/prog/www/tcp/documents/TCP24-English2008.pdf | format = PDF | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

